<% content_for(:title, "Help Centre - Crewbnb") %>
<% meta_description "Find answers to common questions about booking, hosting, payments, and your Crewbnb account." %>

<%# ===== HERO ===== %>
<section class="bg-[#001949] pt-10 pb-16">
  <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto px-6">
    <p class="text-blue-200/60 text-sm font-medium mb-2">Help Centre</p>
    <h1 class="font-headline text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-white leading-[1.1] tracking-tight mb-4 max-w-2xl">
      How can we help?
    </h1>
    <p class="text-blue-200/80 text-base md:text-lg max-w-lg">
      Find answers to common questions about booking, hosting, payments, and more.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<%# ===== QUICK LINKS ===== %>
<section class="bg-white py-16 border-b border-slate-100">
  <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto px-6">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
      <a href="#booking" class="bg-slate-50 rounded-2xl p-6 border border-slate-100 hover:border-slate-200 transition-colors text-center">
        <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-[#001949] text-2xl mb-3 block">luggage</span>
        <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm">Booking</p>
      </a>
      <a href="#hosting" class="bg-slate-50 rounded-2xl p-6 border border-slate-100 hover:border-slate-200 transition-colors text-center">
        <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-[#001949] text-2xl mb-3 block">home_work</span>
        <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm">Hosting</p>
      </a>
      <a href="#payments" class="bg-slate-50 rounded-2xl p-6 border border-slate-100 hover:border-slate-200 transition-colors text-center">
        <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-[#001949] text-2xl mb-3 block">payments</span>
        <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm">Payments</p>
      </a>
      <a href="#account" class="bg-slate-50 rounded-2xl p-6 border border-slate-100 hover:border-slate-200 transition-colors text-center">
        <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-[#001949] text-2xl mb-3 block">person</span>
        <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm">Account</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<%# ===== BOOKING FAQ ===== %>
<section id="booking" class="bg-white py-16 border-b border-slate-100 scroll-mt-20">
  <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-8">
        <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-[#001949] text-xl">luggage</span>
        <h2 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Booking</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-5">
        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">How do I book a stay?</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Search for stays near your job site, pick one that fits, set your dates and team size, then pay. The whole thing takes about 2 minutes.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">Can I book for multiple workers?</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Yes. When searching, set your team size and we'll only show properties with enough beds. You book the whole property for your crew.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">Can I book just weekdays (Monday to Friday)?</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Absolutely — that's what we're built for. Set your check-in as Monday and check-out as Friday. Weekday pricing means you don't pay for nights you don't need.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">How do I cancel a booking?</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Go to your bookings page and select the booking you'd like to cancel. Each property has its own cancellation policy, which you can see before you book.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">How do I contact my host?</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Use the messaging feature on Crewbnb. Go to your booking and click "Message host", or find your conversations under Messages in the menu.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<%# ===== HOSTING FAQ ===== %>
<section id="hosting" class="bg-slate-50 py-16 border-b border-slate-100 scroll-mt-20">
  <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-8">
        <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-[#001949] text-xl">home_work</span>
        <h2 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Hosting</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-5">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">How do I list my property?</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Sign up as a host, then use the host dashboard to add your property. Include photos, pricing, amenities, and a description. Properties are reviewed before going live.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">What kind of properties work best?</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Properties near industrial areas, construction zones, or business parks. Workers care about bed count, parking, fast WiFi, and laundry facilities — not hot tubs.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">How much should I charge?</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">You set your own pricing. Weekday rates are typically lower than tourist rates but you'll get longer, more consistent bookings. Check comparable properties in your area for guidance.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">What if a guest damages my property?</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Report any damage through the messaging system within 48 hours of checkout. Include photos. We'll work with you and the guest to resolve it.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<%# ===== PAYMENTS FAQ ===== %>
<section id="payments" class="bg-white py-16 border-b border-slate-100 scroll-mt-20">
  <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-8">
        <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-[#001949] text-xl">payments</span>
        <h2 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Payments & Invoices</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-5">
        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">How do I pay?</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">We accept all major credit and debit cards. Payment is taken when you confirm your booking.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">Do I get an invoice?</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Yes, every booking generates a proper invoice with a unique reference number. You can find it in your booking details. Send it straight to your accountant.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">When do hosts get paid?</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Hosts receive payment after the guest checks in. Payments are processed securely through our payment provider.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">What's the cancellation refund policy?</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Refund amounts depend on the host's cancellation policy and how far in advance you cancel. Check the listing for specific terms before booking.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<%# ===== ACCOUNT FAQ ===== %>
<section id="account" class="bg-slate-50 py-16 scroll-mt-20">
  <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-8">
        <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-[#001949] text-xl">person</span>
        <h2 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Account</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-5">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">How do I create an account?</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Click "Sign up" in the top menu. Enter your email and password. If you want to list a property, sign up as a host.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">I forgot my password</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Click "Log in" then "Forgot your password?" and enter your email. We'll send you a link to reset it.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">Can I be both a guest and a host?</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Your account is set up as either a guest or a host when you sign up. Contact us if you need to change your role or want to do both.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<%# ===== STILL NEED HELP ===== %>
<section class="bg-white py-16 border-t border-slate-100">
  <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
    <h2 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Still need help?</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-6">Can't find what you're looking for? Get in touch and we'll sort it.</p>
    <%= link_to contact_path, class: "inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-[#001949] text-white px-7 py-3 rounded-xl font-semibold text-sm hover:bg-[#002d75] transition-colors" do %>
      <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-lg">mail</span>
      Contact us
    <% end %>
  </div>
</section>
